         libltdl3, tinylogin, debconf, grub, syslinux, squashfs-tools, pciutils, 
         mknbi, dropbear, ltspfs-client | ltspfsd, genisoimage | mkisofs, 
         xfonts-base, xfonts-100dpi, portmap, acpid,
         ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Conflicts: tcosmonitor (<< 0.1.23.2), tcos (<< 0.89.26)
Recommends: pulseaudio, pulseaudio-utils
Description: tools for generating a thin client bootable image: TCOS
 This package contains tools to create and boot an initramfs for prepackaged
 2.6 Linux kernel. The initramfs is an cpio archive. At boot time, the kernel
 unpacks that archive into ram, mounts and uses it as initial root file system.
 From there thin client configure some hardware, download extra tools 
 ( /usr dir ) and connect to remote server using XMDCP, SSH -X, FreeNX, 
 rDesktop...
 .
 TCOS Thin client support for initramfs-tools.

